[x] explain where profiles show up: `man nix-profiles`
    - environment.systemPackages go into profile /nix/var/nix/profiles/system
    - users.users.auser.packages go into profile /etc/profiles/per-user/auser
    - imperatively installed packages by default go into
      ${XDG_STATE_HOME:-~/.local/state}/nix/profiles/profile
    - root's packages go into ${NIX_STATE_DIR:-/nix/var/nix}/profiles/per-user/root
